		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Impaling Fate",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> the apispeier has at least one creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed} with Grasping Hands or Tail Jab;</p><hr /><p>the apispeier impales a creature on one of the metal spikes on its body plate, dealing @Damage[11d6[piercing]] damage. Target creature must attempt at a @Check[reflex|dc:45] save</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> the creature takes no damage and frees themselves, moving in a free space within 5 feet of the apispeier.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> the creature takes half damage and frees themselves, moving in a free space within 5 feet of the apispeier.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> the creature takes full damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} due to the spikes.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> as failure, but the creature takes also @Damage[2d12[fire,persistent]] damage</p>",
					"gm": ""
				},
